  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean, bounded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Operating envelope is explicitly bounded: flow rates 1–7 L/min, impeller speeds 2000–4500 RPM, fluid temperature 37 ± 1 °C, hematocrit 35–45 %, pump inlet pressure 5–15 mmHg. All 13 credibility factors assessed; all achieved levels meet or exceed required levels. Decision: Accepted.",
